Mean time To patch (Highly exploitable CVE)
unit
children.chars: days on average to patch highly-exploitable CVEs

children.name: Text label
children.chars:
The MTTP is calculated by examining all recently patched endpoints and averages the time taken to apply the latest major OS patch on supported Windows platforms. Since the MTTP only examines recently-patched endpoints, you should also compare the MTTP with the Average Unpatched Time. The Average Unpatched Time examines all unpatched endpoints that do not have patch events.
Learn more

children.name: unit
children.chars: days on average that highly exploitable CVEs remain unpatched

children.name: Text label
children.chars:
The Average Unpatched Time (AUT) is calculated by examining all endpoints vulnerable to highly exploitable CVEs. The AUT applies only to supported Windows platforms and major patch releases. Since the AUT only examines unpatched endpoints that do not have the latest patch, you should also compare the Average Unpatched Time with the MTTP. The MTTP provides data regarding your recently-patched endpoints.
Learn more

children.name: unit
children.chars: of your endpoints contain highly-exploitable CVEs.

children.name: Text label
children.chars:
The Vulnerable Endpoint Percentage applies to all endpoints with Vulnerability Detection enabled. The percentage is calculated from the total number of endpoints with highly-exploitable CVEs divided by the total number of supported endpoints. The Highly-Exploitable CVE Density and Vulnerable Endpoint Percentage work together to help you tailor your response to vulnerable endpoint risks.
Learn more

children.name: Text label
children.chars:
The Highly Exploitable CVE Density is calculated from the total number of detected highly-exploitable CVEs divided by the total number of endpoints with Vulnerability Detection enabled (Total CVEs / Total endpoints with Vulnerability Detection). The density calculation includes operating system and application CVEs.
Learn more

children.name: Text label
children.chars:
Devices that run versions of the Windows operating system that have already reached End of Service (EOS) are more vulnerable to attack as no new security patches are available for newly identified CVEs. 

For more information, check the Microsoft website:
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/lifecycle/products/
